column5: Taking my 4th trip into quetico this year, and am interested in any opinions on the best walleye lakes? Have hit quite a few (bud,bisk, narrows,art) but just looking for somehing new this year? Any suggestions?

Are you going in from the Atikokan side or Ely? I can speak to the Ely side and for easy entry it is hard to beat Basswood, especially the Merriam Bay area, Birch is also good. If you canoe in some, Crooked Lake is topnotch.
